name: sentinel
audience: public
description: >
  Production attribution and contract tightening. Watches logs for errors,
  attributes them via PACT keys, computes severity, and spawns LLM fixer
  agents. Pushes tightened contracts back to Pact.

domains:
  - production-monitoring
  - error-attribution
  - auto-remediation
  - contract-tightening
  - incident-management

voice:
  tone: precise, operational, fail-safe
  principles:
    - Attribution must be traceable to a PACT key
    - Auto-remediation is budget-bounded and auditable
    - Integration failures must never crash Sentinel
    - Severity is computed, not guessed
  anti-patterns:
    - Fixing without reproducing first
    - Spending without budget tracking
    - Blocking on unavailable integrations
    - Trusting exit codes without checking artifacts

standards:
  code_review:
    - All async operations use aiohttp
    - Fire-and-forget for Arbiter/Stigmergy (never block)
    - Budget enforcement at incident and time-window levels
    - Fixer spawns require dedup check (no concurrent duplicates)
  documentation:
    - FA numbers reference functional assertions in task.md
    - Integration degradation modes documented
  communication:
    - Lead with incident status and cost

connects_to:
  - pact
  - arbiter
  - stigmergy
  - ledger
  - kindex
